BLUETONGUE - EUROPE (53): HUNGARY, CONFIRMED, OIE
***********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

Date: 15 Sep 2008
Source: OIE WAHID Weekly Disease Information Vol. 21 - No. 38 [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/wahid-prod/public.php?page=weekly_report_index&admin=0>


Bluetongue, Hungary
----------------------
Information received on 15 Sep 2008 from Dr Miklos Suth, Acting Chief
Veterinary Officer, Animal Health and Food Control Department,
Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Development, Budapest, Hungary

Summary
Report type: Immediate notification
Start date 25 Aug 2008
Date of 1st confirmation of the event 27 Aug 2008
Report date 15 Sep 2008
Date submitted to OIE 15 Sep 2008
Reason for notification: 1st occurrence of a listed disease
Causal agent: Bluetongue virus
Serotype: Pending
Nature of diagnosis: Laboratory (basic), Laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to: the whole country

New outbreaks
Outbreak 1 Gelej, Mezokovesdi, BORSOD-ABAUJ-ZEMPLEN
Date of start of the outbreak 25 Aug 2008
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Farm
Affected animals
Species Cattle
Susceptible 379
Cases 4
Deaths 0
Destroyed 4
Slaughtered 0

Affected population: The total number of affected animals is 379,
including 92 animals that arrived from France.

Summary of outbreaks: Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak statistics
Species Cattle
Apparent morbidity rate 1.06 percent
Apparent mortality rate 0.00 percent
Apparent case fatality rate 0.00 percent
Proportion susceptible animals lost* 1.06 percent
* Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction
and/or slaughter

Epidemiology:
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection
Introduction of new live animals, Legal movement of animals

Epidemiological comments:
The infection is most likely caused by cattle delivered from France.

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type:
Veterinary Diagnostic Directorate of CAO (National laboratory)

Species Cattle
Test antibody detection ELISA
Test date 27 Aug 2008
Result Positive

Laboratory name and type: Veterinary Diagnostic Directorate of
Central Agricultural Office (National laboratory)

Species Cattle
Test polymerase chain reaction (PCR)
Test date 5 Sep 2008
Result Positive

Future Reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>

[This confirms the previous report but still does not give us a BT
type, which is still pending. Again, we suspect it will be BT-8,
representing an eastward spread of the virus.

A map can be obtained from the OIE website report referenced above or
using the zoom out function at
<http://www.1hungary.com/map/gelej>.
- Mod.PC]
